Vice President Joe Biden announced several key staff appointments on March 23, 2009. The appointments include Edward DeSeve as Special Advisor to the President, Assistant to the Vice President, and Special Advisor to the OMB Director for Implementation of the Recovery Act. DeSeve will focus on coordinating efforts at OMB and ensuring the quick and effective implementation of the Recovery Act. Jon Wolfsthal was appointed as Special Advisor to the Vice President for nonproliferation, where he will provide support on nuclear nonproliferation and global nuclear security. Herro Mustafa joined the Vice President's staff as Special Advisor for the Middle East and South Asia, while Matt Teper became the Speechwriter for the Vice President. Kirsten White was appointed as the Policy Director for Dr. Jill Biden.